# BROWSER-core.md - PH Global Rules



**Global rules:**
- `evaluate()` for all browser interaction: data extraction, text input, clicks, state checks
- PH editor = TipTap/ProseMirror (`.tiptap.ProseMirror`). NEVER set `textContent`/`innerHTML`/`value` — use `execCommand('insertText')`
- `click` takes ref as **positional argument**, not an option:
  ```
  curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/click -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"selector":"e1"}'
  ```
  ❌ `click --ref e1` — fails ("unknown option --ref")
  ✅ `click e1` — correct positional argument
- Embed waits at START of each evaluate: `await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000))`
  ```
  curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"fn":"function(){return document.title;}"}'
  ```
  ❌ `--fn /tmp/script.js` — fails (reads literal string, not file)
  ❌ heredoc piped to `--fn` — fails ("Invalid regular expression flags")
  ✅ `--fn 'function(){...}'` — correct inline syntax
- `open` for navigation, NOT `navigate`:
  ```
  curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/open -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"url":"https://example.com"}'
  ```
  ❌ `navigate --url "..."` — fails ("missing required argument 'url'")
  ✅ `open "URL"` — correct positional argument

## Recovery Rules

- Browser timeout → close tab, reopen URL. If fails → `exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/start`, wait 3s, retry once. Do not kill Chrome.
- "matched N elements" error → selector too broad, use narrower selector
- evaluate() unexpected data → check URL, re-navigate if wrong page
- Click fails → retry via evaluate. Still fails → skip, log Error
- Retry also fails → skip, log Error, move to next task
